verbose_text: However, the myogenin expression levels in cells cultured in SKGM-2 medium decreased between passages 2 and 3, indicating that the cells may be entering the early myocyte stage, whereas the myogenin expression levels in cells cultured in DFEFH medium increased between passages 2 and 3 and finally decreased at passage 7 (XREF_FIG), indicating that these conditions may cause the cells to remain at the early differentiating myoblast stage much longer by decreasing myostatin expression levels.
